dependent.value:
The dependent variable is participants’ pragmatism-idealism tendency.

Specifically, we will ask participants “Will you choose a job that fits your interest but pays less, over another job that pays more but does not fit your interest ?” and “Will you quit your job and take a year off from work to travel around the world if it is financially feasible for you to do so ?” 

The higher tendency of choosing a job that fits their interest but pays less indicates that participants are more idealistic, less pragmatic; The higher tendency of quitting their job and take a year off from work to travel around the world indicates that participants are more idealistic, less pragmatic;

